59	2	A 60-year-old patient presents with sudden onset severe eye pain, redness, blurred vision, and markedly elevated intraocular pressure. What is the most likely diagnosis?	Open-angle glaucoma	Angle-closure glaucoma	Uveitis	Cataract	B	Acute angle-closure glaucoma: complete pupillary block causing abrupt Anterior Chamber angle closure and rapid IOP. Presents with severe eye pain, conjunctival erythema, sudden vision loss, halos around lights, headache, fixed and mid-dilated pupil, nausea and vomiting.	5	2026-07-12 00:29:31.936483	\N
