70	2	A patient develops intestinal ischemia leading to necrosis of the bowel. On gross examination, the affected segment appears congested and hemorrhagic. What type of infarct is most likely present?	Pale infarct	Red infarct	White infarct	No infarct	B	Red infarcts - Occurs in venous occlusion and tissues with multiple blood supplies e.g., liver, lung, intestine, testes and with reperfusion (e.g., after angioplasty). White infarcts - Occurs in solid organs with a single (end arterial) blood supply e.g., heart, kidney---	6	2026-07-12 00:29:56.843336	\N
