495	3	Which substance does not cross the placenta, and is also a major form of maternal energy storage?	Triglycerides	Measles antibodies (IgG)	Fatty acids	IgG	A	Triglycerides are too large and hydrophobic to cross the placenta directly. Instead, they are broken down in maternal blood into free fatty acids + glycerol, which can be transferred.	63	2026-07-13 02:19:35.05775	\N
