497	3	A patient presents with photosensitivity, blistering skin lesions on sun-exposed areas, and dark-colored urine. Which enzyme deficiency is most likely responsible?	Porphobilinogen deaminase	Uroporphyrinogen decarboxylase	ALA synthase	Ferrochelatase	B	This is Porphyria cutanea tarda. Key points:\n• Caused by deficiency of uroporphyrinogen decarboxylase\n• Leads to accumulation of uroporphyrins in skin and urine	63	2026-07-13 02:19:35.05775	\N
