732	3	Vasoconstriction in blood vessels is primarily mediated by which receptor?	α1 (alpha-1 adrenergic receptor)	D1 (Dopamine-1 receptor)	β2 (Beta-2 adrenergic receptor)	M3 muscarinic receptor	A	This is Alpha-1 adrenergic receptor\n• Activation of α1 receptors -> smooth muscle contraction -> vasoconstriction\n• Mechanism: Gq -> ↑ IP3 -> ↑ Ca2+ -> contraction	99	2026-07-13 03:07:34.881424	\N
