743	3	110. An elderly patient presents with chronic back pain. Imaging shows bone deformity and mixed lytic and sclerotic lesions with thickened, "cotton wool" appearance of bone. What is the most likely diagnosis?	Osteoporosis	Osteoarthritis	Paget disease of bone	Osteomyelitis	C	This is Paget disease of bone. Key features: Bone pain (especially back pain in elderly), Bone enlargement and deformity, Mixed lytic and sclerotic lesions, "Cotton wool" skull appearance (classic)	100	2026-07-13 03:08:19.424007	\N
