745	3	112. A patient receiving chemotherapy develops severe nausea and vomiting. Which drug is most commonly used as first-line prophylaxis?	Metoclopramide	Ondansetron	Promethazine	Domperidone	B	This is Ondansetron. Mechanism: Blocks 5-HT3 (serotonin) receptors. Acts on: GI vagal afferents, Chemoreceptor trigger zone (CTZ)	100	2026-07-13 03:08:19.424007	\N
746	3	113. A 65-year-old patient with Parkinson disease is started on levodopa therapy. After some time, he develops jaundice and elevated liver enzymes. Which of the following statements is most appropriate regarding this drug?	Levodopa commonly causes severe, irreversible hepatotoxicity	Levodopa is not metabolized in the liver	Levodopa is mainly metabolized peripherally and rarely associated with liver dysfunction	Levodopa directly damages bile ducts in most patients	C	This is Levodopa. Key pharmacology: Levodopa is converted to dopamine in peripheral tissues and CNS. Metabolized mainly by dopa decarboxylase and COMT pathways. Hepatic involvement: Metabolism involves the liver, but clinically significant hepatotoxicity is rare.	100	2026-07-13 03:08:19.424007	\N
