750	3	117. A 10-year-old child presents with short stature (dwarfism) but normal intelligence. Laboratory tests show low IGF-1 (somatomedin C) levels despite normal or high growth hormone levels. Which of the following is the most likely underlying problem?	Excess somatostatin secretion	GH receptor resistance	Excess somatomedin production	Thyroid hormone deficiency	B	This is Somatomedin C (IGF-1). Growth hormone pathway: GH -> stimulates liver -> produces IGF-1 (somatomedin C). IGF-1 -> responsible for linear bone growth	100	2026-07-13 03:08:19.424007	\N
