752	3	A patient is diagnosed with a thyroid carcinoma. Which of the following is a rare site of metastasis for thyroid tumors?	Bone	Brain	Liver	Gastrointestinal tract	D	This is Thyroid carcinoma\n• Common metastasis sites for thyroid cancers:\n• Lungs (very common, especially follicular carcinoma)\n• Bone\n• Brain (less common but possible)\n• Liver (can occur in advanced disease)\nRare site:\n• Gastrointestinal (GI) tract metastasis is very rare	101	2026-07-13 03:08:59.607793	\N
753	3	A patient who recently visited a rural village develops malaise, fatigue, anorexia, and generalized weakness for a few days, followed by mild jaundice. Liver function tests show elevated ALT and AST. What is the most likely diagnosis?	Fatty liver disease	Acute viral hepatitis	Liver cirrhosis	Gallstones	B	This is Acute viral hepatitis\nKey features:\n• Exposure risk (rural/village contaminated food/water)\n• Prodromal symptoms: malaise, fatigue, anorexia\n• Followed by jaundice\n• Elevated ALT/AST (hepatocellular injury pattern)	101	2026-07-13 03:08:59.607793	\N
754	3	A patient with a history of sickle cell disease presents with Howell-Jolly bodies seen on peripheral blood smear. What is the most likely associated condition?	Hypersplenism	Hyposplenism (functional asplenia)	Acute hemolytic anemia	Iron deficiency anemia	B	This is Hyposplenism\n• Howell-Jolly bodies = nuclear remnants in RBCs\n• Normally removed by spleen -> their presence indicates:\n• Absent or poorly functioning spleen	101	2026-07-13 03:08:59.607793	\N
755	3	A child presents with perianal itching, especially at night. Examination reveals fine thread-like white worms around the anus. What is the drug of choice?	Metronidazole	Albendazole	Praziquantel	Ivermectin	B	This is Enterobiasis (pinworm infection)\n• Causative organism: Enterobius vermicularis (pinworm)\nKey features:\n• Perianal itching at night\n• "Thread-like white worms"	101	2026-07-13 03:08:59.607793	\N
756	3	Vitamin D3 (cholecalciferol) is obtained from which source?	Plant origin (UV-exposed plants)	Animal origin (skin synthesis and animal sources)	Bacterial origin	Fungal origin only	B	This is Vitamin D3 (cholecalciferol)\nVitamin D exists in two main forms:\n• D2 (ergocalciferol) -> plant/fungal origin\n• D3 (cholecalciferol) -> animal origin + human skin	101	2026-07-13 03:08:59.607793	\N
757	3	In primary hyperparathyroidism (excess PTH), which vitamin D metabolite is increased?	1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D (calcitriol)	25-hydroxyvitamin D	24,25-dihydroxyvitamin D	Vitamin D3 (cholecalciferol)	A	This is Parathyroid hormone\nPTH acts on kidney:\n• ↑ 1α-hydroxylase activity in proximal tubule\nThis converts:\n• 25-hydroxyvitamin D -> 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D (calcitriol)	101	2026-07-13 03:08:59.607793	\N
758	3	Child presents with ambiguous genitalia. Karyotype is 46,XX, and there is mild virilization at birth. There is no severe salt-wasting crisis. What is the most likely enzyme deficiency?	17α-hydroxylase deficiency	21-hydroxylase deficiency	11β-hydroxylase deficiency	5α-reductase deficiency	B	This is Congenital adrenal hyperplasia due to 21-hydroxylase deficiency\nMechanism:\n• ↓ 21-hydroxylase ->\n• ↓ cortisol\n• ↓ aldosterone (variable severity)\n• ↑ ACTH -> adrenal hyperplasia\n• ↑ androgen production	101	2026-07-13 03:08:59.607793	\N
759	3	A researcher follows two groups of cancer patients over time and plots the probability of survival against time, showing stepwise drops whenever a patient dies. Which statistical tool is being used?	Bell curve	Kaplan-Meier survival curve	ROC curve	Scatter plot	B	This is Kaplan-Meier survival curve\n• Used to show time-to-event data (e.g., death, relapse)	101	2026-07-13 03:08:59.607793	\N
760	3	The sleep-wake cycle is primarily controlled by which structure?	Pituitary gland	Hypothalamus	Cerebellum	Thalamus	B	This is Hypothalamus\n• Sleep-wake cycle is regulated by the suprachiasmatic nucleus (SCN) in the hypothalamus\n• SCN acts as the biological clock (circadian rhythm center)	101	2026-07-13 03:08:59.607793	\N
