762	3	A patient presents with hirsutism, weight gain, and headaches. Laboratory tests suggest elevated cortisol levels. Which of the following is the most likely cause?	Exogenous glucocorticoid use	ACTH-secreting tumor (pituitary adenoma)	Primary adrenal insufficiency	Hypothyroidism	B	This is Cushing disease. Key features: Hirsutism (↑ androgens), Headache (pituitary tumor mass effect), ↑ cortisol from adrenal stimulation	102	2026-07-13 03:09:37.907521	\N
