1167	3	Which of the following hormonal profiles is most strongly associated with the pathogenesis of Hyperemesis Gravidarum?	High hCG	Low hCG	Low estrogen	Low progesterone	A	Hyperemesis Gravidarum is linked to elevated levels of hCG or estrogen. This is supported by the fact that the condition is more prevalent in pregnancies with higher hCG concentrations, such as multiple gestations (twins/triplets) or molar pregnancies. The peak of hCG levels typically correlates with the peak of nausea and vomiting symptoms in the first trimester.	151	2026-07-15 01:21:10.494865	\N
